<h1>Aeroway</h1>
<p>These are mainly related to aerodromes, airfields other ground 
facilities that support the operation of airplanes and helicopters. See 
the page Aeroways for an introduction on mapping these features.
</p>
<p>[<b>aeroway</b>=<b>aerodrome</b>]<br>An airport</p>
<p>[<b>aeroway</b>=<b>apron</b>]<br>An area of an airport where planes are parked, unloaded or loaded, refueled, or boarded</p>
<p>[<b>aeroway</b>=<b>gate</b>]<br>A gate number at an airport where passengers wait before boarding their flight</p>
<p>[<b>aeroway</b>=<b>hangar</b>]<br>A large airport building with extensive floor areas for housing aircraft or spacecraft</p>
<p>[<b>aeroway</b>=<b>helipad</b>]<br>A landing area or platform for helicopters</p>
<p>[<b>aeroway</b>=<b>heliport</b>]<br>A special aerodrome built for helicopters</p>
<p>[<b>aeroway</b>=<b>navigationaid</b>]<br>A facility that supports visual navigation for aircraft</p>
<p>[<b>aeroway</b>=<b>runway</b>]<br>Runway of an airfield</p>
<p>[<b>aeroway</b>=<b>spaceport</b>]<br>A spaceport (other than airport / heliport)</p>
<p>[<b>aeroway</b>=<b>taxilane</b>]<br>A path in an airport that is part of the aircraft parking area or apron</p>
<p>[<b>aeroway</b>=<b>taxiway</b>]<br>Taxiway of an airfield</p>
<p>[<b>aeroway</b>=<b>terminal</b>]<br>An airport passenger building</p>
<p>[<b>aeroway</b>=<b>windsock</b>]<br>An object that shows pilots wind direction and speed.</p>
